HEADWORD: Rocketer
<hw>Rock"et*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Sporting)</fld>
<def>A bird, especially a pheasant, which, being flushed, rises straight
in the air like a rocket.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rocket scientist</ent>⟦br⟧
